---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "About | Vitalij Hein";
const description =
  "About Vitalij Hein: AI Engineer and Software Architect working across customer discovery, architecture, hands-on implementation, verification, and delivery.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} pageClass="about-page">
  <section class="page-intro">
    <div class="shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">About / Engineering profile</p>
      <h1>I stay close to the system.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        I am an AI Engineer and Software Architect who likes the whole problem:
        understanding what a customer actually needs, choosing the architecture,
        writing the software, proving that it works, and making the result usable by others.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="shell section">
    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="about-block">
        <p class="meta-label">Current role</p>
        <h2>From consulting context to production system</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="about-block">
        <p>
          At Cluster Dynamics Reply, I work as an AI Architect & Engineer on
          enterprise systems. My responsibility commonly spans discovery,
          requirements, solution architecture, implementation, cloud integration,
          testing, stakeholder communication, and handover.
        </p>
        <p>
          At one client, I served as the technical expert for an AI workstream:
          setting direction, coordinating the work of five contributors, and
          supplying the engineering knowledge they needed. That leadership work is
          distinct from projects such as the secure construction knowledge system,
          which I conceived and delivered independently.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-block">
        <p class="meta-label">Engineering profile</p>
        <h2>AI systems built on software fundamentals</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="about-block">
        <p>
          My work is AI-focused, but not AI-only. I have developed software since
          2017 and work across Python, C#, backend services, APIs, retrieval systems,
          automated testing, data flows, and Azure cloud integration. The model is
          one component; the surrounding software determines whether the system can
          be trusted in production.
        </p>
        <ul class="principles">
          <li>Make boundaries and failure modes explicit.</li>
          <li>Prefer evidence from real system behavior over demo confidence.</li>
          <li>Use the simplest architecture that meets the actual constraints.</li>
          <li>Keep technical decisions explainable to customers and teams.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="about-block">
        <p class="meta-label">Agentic Engineering</p>
        <h2>Controlled leverage, not autonomous theater</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="about-block">
        <p>
          I design agentic delivery systems as engineering infrastructure:
          bounded context, isolated workspaces, explicit state, task-aware model
          routing, automated gates, independent review, and human ownership of
          scope and release decisions. This lets me explore and implement quickly
          without lowering the standard of evidence required from the result.
        </p>
        <p>
          The important capability is not producing more code. It is making better
          decisions across more of the delivery path while remaining accountable
          for what reaches production.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-block research-note">
        <p class="meta-label">Research & recognition</p>
        <h2>Model engineering before the current wave</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="about-block">
        <p>
          For my TU Wien diploma thesis, I fine-tuned specialized BERT, RoBERTa,
          and OPT variants for 18 propaganda techniques and combined them with a
          meta-classifier. The system improved Micro-F1 from a 0.54 baseline to
          0.78. I was also part of the Reply and Riverty team that won the
          Microsoft AI Challenge 2025 with a self-correcting customer-service workflow.
        </p>
        <div class="actions">
          <a class="button" href="https://repositum.tuwien.at/handle/20.500.12708/188206" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
            Read the thesis ↗
          </a>
          <a class="button" href="https://github.com/vitalijhein/engineering-case-studies" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
            Explore case studies ↗
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section closing">
    <div class="shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Difficult problem? Good.</p>
      <h2>Bring me into the technical conversation.</h2>
      <p>
        I am most useful where customer context, architecture, and hands-on
        engineering have to meet.
      </p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button button-primary" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/vitalijhein" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
          Connect on LinkedIn ↗
        </a>
        <a class="button" href="mailto:vitalijhein@googlemail.com">Write an email</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
